# Datatree (Cursor — legacy .cursorrules)

> NOTE: This is the legacy single-file format. Cursor 0.45+ prefers
> `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` (also installed by datatree). When both exist,
> the .mdc files win. This file is kept for backward compatibility.

Datatree is a persistent, incrementally-updated knowledge graph of this
project, exposed to Cursor via the `datatree` MCP server (see
`.cursor/mcp.json`). A per-user daemon (`datatree-supervisor`) keeps the
graph fresh in the background.

## Tool usage rules

**Use datatree MCP tools BEFORE Cursor's built-in code search, file
read, or @-symbol lookup** for structural or semantic questions about
this codebase. Use built-in tools only when datatree suggests them or
to read a specific file datatree returned.

On every task:

1. `datatree.minimal_context(task="<description>")` — ~100 tokens.
2. Iterate via `datatree.query`, `datatree.impact`, `datatree.search`
   with `detail_level="minimal"`.
3. Only then read files; budget <= 5 calls and <= 800 tokens per task.
4. Edits trigger incremental graph updates via the afterFileEdit hook.

## Step ledger

Steps stream to `~/.datatree/projects/<id>/steps.jsonl`. Recover with
`datatree.last_steps(n=10)` after any context loss.

## Drift detection

Datatree flags symbol/doc/test drift. Address all flags before done.

## Compaction resilience

If Cursor truncates the conversation, re-prime with one
`datatree.minimal_context(...)` call. State lives in the graph, not chat.
